      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the<strong> red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop each half in half again so that you are left with 4<span class=\"text-danger\"> [8] </span>pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> pepper quarters</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and put the tray in the oven for an initial 18 min</p>",
